LG Uplus Shares Jump Most in 22 Months in Seoul on Smartphone Speculation

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-03-08T05:02:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/lg-uplus-shares-jump-most-in-22-months-in-seoul-on-smartphone-speculation.html
  LG Uplus Corp. (032640)  jumped the most in 22
months in Seoul trading on speculation the company’s smartphone
subscribers are increasing faster than expected, an analyst
said.  The South Korean mobile-phone operator jumped 8.2 percent
to 5,950 won as of 1:56 p.m. on the Korea Exchange, while the
benchmark Kospi stock index climbed 1.3 percent.  “Faster-than-expected growth of smartphone subscribers
will lead to an earnings turnaround this year,” Stan Jung, an
analyst at Woori Investment & Securities Co., said by phone
today. He said the shares are “cheap.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
